# NestJS Test Conventions

## File Location

Unit test specs live in `apps/server/test/<module>/`, NOT next to source files.

```
src/users/repository/users.repository.ts       ← source
test/users/repository/users.repository.spec.ts ← test (not src/users/)
```

## Import Aliases

Always use `@/` (maps to `src/`) — never relative paths.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
import { UsersRepository } from '@/users/repository/users.repository';
import { PrismaService } from '@/prisma/prisma.service';

// ❌ BAD
import { UsersRepository } from '../users/repository/users.repository';
import { PrismaService } from 'src/prisma/prisma.service';
```

## Mock Boundaries

Mock only true boundaries. In a service test, mock the repository. In a repository test, mock `PrismaService`.

```typescript
// Service spec — mock repository
const mockRepository: jest.Mocked<UsersRepository> = {
  findAll: jest.fn(),
  findOne: jest.fn(),
  create: jest.fn(),
  update: jest.fn(),
} as unknown as jest.Mocked<UsersRepository>;

// Repository spec — mock PrismaService
const mockPrisma = {
  user: {
    findMany: jest.fn(),
    findUniqueOrThrow: jest.fn(),
    create: jest.fn(),
    update: jest.fn(),
  },
};
```

## Mock Data

Mock objects must include ALL model fields (including `updatedAt`) to satisfy Prisma-generated types.

```typescript
const mockUser = {
  id: 'user-1',
  email: 'test@example.com',
  name: 'Test User',
  role: 'user',
  createdAt: new Date(),
  updatedAt: new Date(), // ← required by Prisma model
};
```

## Spec Structure

```typescript
describe('UsersRepository', () => {
  let repository: UsersRepository;

  beforeEach(() => {
    jest.clearAllMocks();
    repository = new UsersRepository(mockPrisma as unknown as PrismaService);
  });

  describe('findAll', () => {
    it('returns users ordered by createdAt desc', async () => { ... });
  });

  describe('findOne', () => {
    it('returns a user by id', async () => { ... });
    it('throws when user is not found', async () => { ... });
  });
});
```

## Minimum Test Cases Per Feature

1. Happy path
2. Invalid input / guard / not-found case
3. Dependency failure (for repository tests)
